race.comment: MAGNOLIA SKY (1) is a progressive type and has scored at her last two, the latest over 1100m at this track. Gets in well again with the 3kg claim and she can deliver the hat-trick. ANTHEIA (3) went close at Launceston on-pace and then jumped for the 13 gate here and caught the eye coming from the tail, winning a CL1 this trip. Draws inside today and is decent chance to repeat the dose. BILLIE THE GREAT (6) was second up last start and went close when beaten half a length at Launceston over 1200m. Had won a CL1 here prior first up and should be right in it with the extra fitness. RARE ORO (9) went well enough first up to consider.
